messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/users/logout

All methods acceptable?
- false

HTTP methods (based on the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- server.js mounts the users router at the prefix /api/users: app.use('/api/users', userRoutes).
- In routes/userRoutes.js the logout route is defined as router.post('/logout', logoutUser). Combined with the mount prefix this yields /api/users/logout and only a POST handler is registered for that path.
- No HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE or PATCH handlers are defined for this path in the provided code; per the instruction I only considered what the code explicitly registers, so those methods are marked false.
- "All methods acceptable" is false because the code only registers POST for this endpoint.
